description: The sadistic crimes of Ian Brady and Myra Hindley shocked the nation to its core.
title: How the Moors murders by Ian Brady and Myra Hindley shocked the nation

author: Charles Clark
description: Brady and his partner, Myra Hindley, were jailed in 1966 after torturing and murdering five children together.
title: Moors murderer Ian Brady has died aged 79

author: Steve Robson, Stephen White
description: The Moors Murderer rejected suggestions that he had 'manipulated' Myra Hindley into carrying out their murderous spree
title: Ian Brady's confessions including how Myra was 'in tune' with him from the start

author: Sophie Evans
description: He conspired with his then lover Myra Hindley to torture and kill five children in the 1960s - with three of their dead bodies being found on a moor in the Peak District
title: Twisted Moors Murderer's horrific crimes and sickening 51-year silence

author: Frances Perraudin
description: Murderer’s solicitor assures coroner that 79-year-old’s remains will not end up on moors where he and Myra Hindley buried victims
title: Ian Brady's ashes will not be scattered on Saddleworth Moor, lawyer confirms

author: By Sam Tonkin For Mailonline
description: Chief Insp Ian Hanson (pictured), who grew up in the area of Manchester where Brady and his lover Myra Hindley committed their heinous crimes, said the 'monster' should be left to 'rot'.
title: Calls for Ian Brady's body to be left in an unmarked grave

author: By James Tozer, Ian Drury for the Daily Mail, Abe Hawken and Thomas Burrows
description: Moors murderer Ian Brady (pictured), who killed five children alongside his co-accused Myra Hindley in the 1960s, has died after suffering from inoperable lung cancer, Ashworth Hospital has confirmed.
title: Moors murderer Ian Brady is dead aged 79

author: Alison Smith-Squire
description: Tommy Rhattigan has broken his self-imposed 50-year silence to tell how Myra Hindley persuaded him to go home with her and her sadistic lover in 1963
title: Potential victim tell how he escaped clutches of Ian Brady

author: By Richard Spillett, Crime Correspondent For Mailonline
description: Ian Brady's fascination with Nazism and sexual perversion would take hold of his younger lover Myra Hindley as they plotted and carried out the abduction, torture and murders of children.
title: How Brady and Hindley's twisted relationship spawned moors murders

author: Michael Holden
description: One of Britain's most notorious killers, "Moors murderer" Ian Brady, who murdered five children with his lover and accomplice Myra Hindley during a sadistic two-year reign of terror in the 1960s died on Monday.
title: Sadistic British child killer, 'Moors Murderer' Ian Brady, dies
